11 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
12 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
13 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Office of
14 Management and Enterprise Services Efficiency Act of 2026".
15 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34.5.1 of Title 62, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services shall be
19 supervised and directed by the Chief Operating Officer.
20 B. The Chief Operating Officer of the Office of Management and
21 Enterprise Services shall organize the Office into functional units
22 as follows:
23 1. Administration;
24 2. Capital Assets Management;
