1 3. Central Purchasing;
2 4. Human Capital Management; and
3 5. Risk Assessment and Compliance.
4 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34.11.1-A of Title 62, unless
6 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 The functions of the Office of Management and Enterprise
8 Services related to information technology shall be supervised by
9 the Chief Information Officer.
10 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 34.34.1 of Title 62, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. The Chief Financial Officer shall perform the duties and
14 responsibilities previously assigned to the Office of Management and
15 Enterprise Services with reporting and analyzing state revenue
16 information and to assist in the presentation and analysis of state
17 revenue information as part of the duties of the State Board of
18 Equalization with respect to the appropriation of public funds
19 pursuant to Section 23 of Article X of the Oklahoma Constitution.
20 B. Upon request by the Governor, the Chief Financial Officer
21 shall provide such assistance as may be required for the preparation
22 of the annual Executive Budget.
