4 with state operations; and
5 4. The ability to organize and present clearly oral and written
6 reports of findings and recommendations.
7 D. The Governor may remove the Chief Operating Officer for good
8 cause shown.
9 E. Any person appointed to the position of Chief Operating
10 Officer pursuant to the provisions of this section shall have full
11 authority to take any actions authorized or required by law pending
12 the confirmation of the person by the Oklahoma State Senate.
