1 Section 921.1. A. The Attorney General shall allocate funds
2 from the Legal Services Revolving Fund to provide legal
3 representation to indigent persons in this state in civil legal
4 matters to the extent that funds are available from the Legal
5 Services Revolving Fund. The Attorney General shall be responsible
6 for allocating these funds pursuant to contract with eligible
7 regional or statewide organizations which ordinarily render legal
8 services to indigent persons. The Attorney General may charge an
9 administrative fee for administering the contracts. The funds shall
10 be allocated for the benefit of indigent clients in all seventy-
11 seven (77) counties of the state on a pro rata basis, utilizing an
12 allocation formula that distributes funds according to the number of
13 residents whose incomes are less than the official United States
14 federal poverty guidelines, based on the United States census data,
15 as a percentage of the total number of these residents in this state
16 and which reserves funds for services for specialized areas of law.
17 B. As used in this section, "eligible organization" means an
18 entity that:
