10 2. The margin of votes between those for the issue and the
11 number required for approval is one percent (1%) or less of the
12 total number of votes cast on the issue when fourteen thousand nine
13 hundred ninety-nine (14,999) or fewer total votes are cast for and
14 against the issue or question.
15 Provided, furthermore, that a recount is authorized only after an
16 individual, who is a registered voter and who participated in the
17 election, presents to the appropriate county election board a
18 petition signed by one hundred fifty (150) registered voters who
19 participated in the election when fifteen thousand (15,000) or more
20 total votes are counted for and against the question, or if fourteen
21 thousand nine hundred ninety-nine (14,999) or fewer votes are cast
22 for and against the issue, by a number of registered voters who
23 participated in the election equal to one percent (1%) or more of
24 the total votes cast for and against the issue.
