10 1. Recognize and support individuals with disabilities by
11 treating them with dignity and respect as productive members of our
12 society in Oklahoma;
13 2. Acknowledge their contributions as productive and
14 independent citizens in the state and the useful work they perform
15 in their local communities;
16 3. Support a service delivery system for individuals with
17 disabilities ensuring that the individuals, their families, or
18 guardians are well informed as to the types of services and
19 resources available to such individuals in order to encourage their
20 independence, self-esteem, and self-worth, regardless of the
21 severity of the disability; and
22 4. Recognize that self-choice on the part of individuals with
23 disabilities is critical and that the most appropriate setting for
24 meeting their needs should be a paramount consideration when
Req. No. 17188 Page 444

