1 B. The Medicaid fraud control unit shall be the state entity to
2 which all cases of suspected Medicaid fraud shall be referred by the
3 Oklahoma Health Care Authority or its fiscal agents for the purposes
4 of investigation, civil action, criminal action or referral to the
5 district attorney. Provided however, nothing contained in the
6 Oklahoma Medicaid Program Integrity Act shall prohibit the Oklahoma
7 Health Care Authority from investigating or additionally referring
8 to other proper law enforcement agencies cases of suspected Medicaid
9 fraud, nor the Attorney General from pursuing cases of suspected
10 Medicaid fraud without a referral from the Oklahoma Health Care
11 Authority if there is credible evidence of fraud. The Oklahoma
12 Health Care Authority shall be authorized to require providers to
13 display information about how to report providers suspected of
14 fraudulent activity relating to the Oklahoma Medicaid Program. The
15 Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall require that signs be posted in
16 any and all locations where services provided by the Oklahoma
17 Medicaid Program are delivered to Medicaid recipients. The sign
18 shall make reference to the Attorney General’s Medicaid Fraud
19 Control Unit hotline and provide the current phone number for the
20 hotline, and shall be placed in a conspicuous location within a
21 provider’s office. The sign shall contain notification that all
22 reports to the hotline may be filed anonymously by persons
23 suspecting fraudulent activity.
