6 required by subsection A of this section.
7 C. The State Board of Equalization shall make the
8 determinations required by subsection A of this section by not later
9 than the fifteenth day immediately following the last day on which
10 the Governor is authorized to veto bills following the close of each
11 regular legislative session. The State Board of Equalization's
12 findings shall be made in a report to the Secretary of State showing
13 the determination for each retirement bill by reference to the
14 respective Senate or House of Representatives number for the bill.
15 The report shall be submitted to the Secretary of State by not later
16 than the last day on which the State Board of Equalization is
17 required to make the determinations. The Secretary of State shall
18 cause the State Board of Equalization's report to be printed in the
19 annual session laws of the State of Oklahoma.
