7 behavioral health facilities to accommodate new licensed acute or
8 residential treatment beds; reallocation of beds from adult acute to
9 child/adolescent acute beds; relocation assistance for licensed
10 behavioral health staff currently living out of state; upskilling
11 existing behavioral health workforce; adding new psychiatric and
12 psychological residencies, internships and post-doctoral training
13 programs; providing social work scholarships; providing mental
14 health nursing scholarships; creating one-time private-sector
15 workforce innovation grants; providing licensure preparation
16 assistance; and creating a behavioral health trauma fund for
17 intensive home and community-based services. Expenditures from the
18 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
19 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director Chief
20 Operating Officer of the Office of Management and Enterprise
21 Services for approval and payment.
22 C. The Oklahoma State University Medical Authority and the
23 University Hospitals Authority shall prepare a report for the
24 Legislature on the results of the first year of funding, including
