3 E. The Task Force shall be authorized to meet as necessary in
4 order to perform the duties imposed upon it. Legislative members of
5 the Task Force shall be reimbursed for travel expenses pursuant to
6 the provisions of Section 456 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
7 Other members of the Task Force shall be reimbursed as provided by
8 the appointing authority.
9 F. The Task Force shall conduct a study regarding all state tax
10 credits regardless of the tax type against which such credit may be
11 claimed and any other economic incentives that affect state or local
12 tax liabilities. The study shall include, but shall not be limited
13 to:
14 1. The justification for the enactment of any state tax credits
15 based upon the relevant economics of the applicable industry or
16 economic sector affected;
17 2. The economic impact related to the utilization of state tax
18 credits;
19 3. Analysis of the utilization of the credits by tax credit
20 purchasers;
21 4. The impact of tax credits on any and all economic sectors of
22 the state economy;
23 5. The adequacy or inadequacy of state tax credits or other
24 economic incentives; and
Req. No. 17188 Page 782

