1 6. Such other matters related to state tax credits or economic
2 incentives as the Task Force deems relevant.
3 G. The Task Force shall be subject to the provisions of:
4 1. The Oklahoma Open Meeting Act; and
5 2. The Oklahoma Open Records Act.
6 H. Staff assistance for the Task Force shall be provided by the
7 staff of the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the State Senate.
8 I. The Task Force shall produce a final written report of its
9 findings and any recommendations regarding transferable tax credits.
10 The report shall be submitted to the Governor, the Speaker of the
11 Oklahoma House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of
12 the State Senate not later than December 31, 2011.
13 J. The provisions of this section shall cease to have the force
14 and effect of law and the Task Force shall terminate effective
15 January 1, 2012.
