13 second-choice consultant shall commence. If the Department or the
14 Authority and the second-choice consultant cannot reach an
15 agreement, their negotiations shall be terminated and negotiations
16 with the third-choice consultant shall commence. If the Department
17 or the Authority and the third-choice consultant cannot reach an
18 agreement, then all negotiations shall be terminated. Should the
19 Department or the Authority be unable to negotiate a satisfactory
20 contract with any of the three selected consultants, the Department
21 or the Authority shall reevaluate the proposed work and send out a
22 new notice.
